## Document Chunking

<!-- How documents are split before embedding. Chunk size and overlap
     affect retrieval quality. Larger chunks preserve more context but
     reduce precision. Overlap prevents information loss at boundaries. -->

- **Chunk size:** {{CHUNK_SIZE}} characters
- **Chunk overlap:** {{CHUNK_OVERLAP}} characters
- **Chunking strategy:** {{CHUNKING_STRATEGY}}

<!-- Chunking strategies:
  - fixed        — Fixed character count. Simple, predictable.
  - paragraph    — Split on double newlines. Preserves natural boundaries.
  - markdown     — Split on headers (## / ###). Best for structured docs.
  - semantic     — Use sentence boundaries. Most accurate but slower.
-->

### Chunking Rules

- Strip HTML comments and template syntax before embedding.
- Preserve code blocks as single chunks when possible.
- Include the source file path and section header as chunk metadata.
- Skip files matching: {{CHUNKING_EXCLUDE_PATTERNS}}

